 or a fork. Make two slits in the center of the pastry to allow steam to escape, then bake for 40-50 minutes (200°C) or until pastry is golden brown. Serve hot."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Gluten Free Pastry","content":["160 g butter, chilled, plus extra for greasing","140 g rice flour","70 g arrowroot flour","90 g cornflour, plus extra for dusting","¼ tsp sea salt","2 tsp xanthan gum","1 egg","1 tsp cider vinegar","40 g water, chilled"]},{"title":"Chicken and pear filling","content":["2 garlic cloves","1 leek, white part only, cut into pieces","50 g butter","600 g chicken thighs, boneless and skinless, cut into cubes (3 cm)","3 sprigs fresh thyme, leaves only","½ tsp ground black pepper","50 g water","2 - 3 tbsp cornflour","1 tbsp vegetable stock paste (see tip)","50 g white wine","150 g pear (approx. 1 pear), peeled, cored and cut into cubes (2 cm)","50 g whipping cream"]}],"id":"r146868","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-UOL1Pm2CTy8\/XZanGqO_47I\/AAAAAAAAg6I\/RqAcRIp4n7ouJrqXnAnDPJ-pDCAbYrysACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_222ij1ierXwBI_zZ.png","title":"Chicken and Pear Pie","publishedAt":"2017-04-24T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"14.5 g","fat":"39.8 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"38.2 g","calories":"2386 kJ \/ 568 kcal"},"usefulItems":"pie dish, cling film, silicone bread mat, rolling pin, baking paper, glass bowl, high-sided pie dish (23 cm), refrigerator, oven","hintsAndTricks":["Please refer to <em>The Basic Cookbook<\/em> or <em>Everyday Cookbook<\/em> for the Vegetable stock paste recipe.","Serve Chicken and pear pie as a hearty meal with your favourite steamed vegetables or salad on the side.","Leftovers store well in a sealable container in the refrigerator for lunches the next day.","To ensure gluten free recipes are gluten free, always read the labels of your products as some may contain traces of wheat or gluten.","For tips on how to blind bake your pastry, please refer to any of the pastry recipes in <em>The Basic Cookbook<\/em> or the f